and then arrests them
for using.

34:14.834 --> 34:16.867
He locks our sons
and daughters in his prisons

34:16.934 --> 34:18.533
and then walks away,

34:18.600 --> 34:20.166
a smile across
his white face.

34:20.233 --> 34:23.700
- Uh, Mrs. Arif,
I hate to...

34:23.767 --> 34:25.700
some of the other passengers
on board have asked me

34:25.767 --> 34:27.633
to ask you if you could
keep your voice down.

34:27.700 --> 34:29.433
-  Why?

34:29.500 --> 34:31.300
Because they don't want
to hear the truth?

34:31.367 --> 34:33.400
The drug policy
in this country

34:33.467 --> 34:35.367
is excessive, oppressive,
and racist!

34:35.433 --> 34:36.667
- Well, be that as it may--

34:36.734 --> 34:38.734
- Instead of locking
young black men behind bars,

34:38.800 --> 34:40.667
we ought to implement
substance abuse treatment,

34:40.734 --> 34:42.834
which is less expensive
and more productive.

34:42.900 --> 34:45.100
- Well, I agree, but now's
not the time--

34:45.166 --> 34:47.300
- When is the time?

34:47.367 --> 34:49.734
Did you know that the number
of inmates in American prisons

34:49.800 --> 34:51.767
has more than tripled
in the last 20 years?

34:51.834 --> 34:53.233
- Yes.

34:53.300 --> 34:55.200
- Did you know that
if the inmate population

34:55.266 --> 34:58.967
continues to grow exponentially,
by the year 2053,

34:59.033 --> 35:02.867
the United States will have
more people in prison than out?

35:02.934 --> 35:04.467
So I ask you, Father.

35:04.533 --> 35:06.867
How long do we wait to
change the way things are?

35:09.367 --> 35:11.600
- Her baby's trying to sleep.

35:18.834 --> 35:20.934
- Your husband's a drug addict?

35:21.000 --> 35:23.867
- He was,
until he found Allah.

35:23.934 --> 35:27.400
- My son, Augustus,
he was too.

35:27.467 --> 35:29.066
- 70% of those arrested

35:29.133 --> 35:31.233
test positive
for substance abuse.

35:31.300 --> 35:33.000
- Ms. Arif--
- Sonsyrea.

35:33.066 --> 35:34.900
- Sonsyrea,

35:34.967 --> 35:38.734
your head's all crammed
with facts and figures.

35:38.800 --> 35:41.066
But a cold, hard fact

35:41.133 --> 35:44.166
is never as good
as the simple truth.

35:46.266 --> 35:48.100
Your husband...

35:48.166 --> 35:51.367
did he hurt you and your
children while he was addicted?

35:52.834 --> 35:55.233
- Yeah, he became a thief.

35:55.300 --> 35:57.133
- And now?

35:57.200 --> 36:01.900
- He struggled and he struggled
and he fought his cravings.

36:01.967 --> 36:04.734
With the help of Allah,
he is clean.

36:04.800 --> 36:06.066
- And your children?

36:06.133 --> 36:09.800
- They miss their father,
but they are blossoming.

36:09.867 --> 36:14.467
- Then, girl, that's the story
you ought to be telling.

36:14.533 --> 36:18.100
That's the stuff
people need to hear.

36:20.934 --> 36:22.333
- You're in a good mood today.

36:22.400 --> 36:23.800
- Yeah, man, my wife's
coming to see me.

36:23.867 --> 36:25.667
- All right, is she bringing
your children?

36:25.734 --> 36:28.934
- No, Sonsyrea and I need
some time, just the two of us.

36:29.900 --> 36:32.400
O'Reily.
That man is an animal.

36:33.900 --> 36:36.266
- He murdered Patrick Keenan
with such brutality,

36:36.333 --> 36:39.133
every time I see him I wonder
how he lives with himself.

36:40.400 --> 36:41.900
- How you doing,
Bismilla?

36:44.000 --> 36:46.300
Eat up, Arif, move it.

36:47.467 --> 36:49.467
Hey, take over here
for a second, okay?

36:49.533 --> 36:50.834
- Where the fuck
is you going, man?

36:52.600 --> 36:54.266
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

36:54.333 --> 36:55.567
- Hey, O'Reily, relax,
I haven't seen your brother

36:55.633 --> 36:57.800
since he checked out
of protective custody.

36:57.867 --> 36:59.033
We just catching up,
man, come on.

36:59.100 --> 37:00.233
- I don't want you
anywhere near him.

37:00.300 --> 37:02.300
- But, Ryan, I like Henry.

37:02.367 --> 37:03.934
- I told you,
this guy's a scumbag.

37:04.000 --> 37:06.333
- It takes one
to know one.

37:06.400 --> 37:07.834
- You on some kind of
a kamikaze mission there,

37:07.900 --> 37:09.066
Stanton, huh?

37:09.133 --> 37:10.333
If I see you talking
to Cyril again,

37:10.400 --> 37:12.133
you're going down
in flames.

37:15.567 --> 37:17.367
- Later.

37:18.600 --> 37:20.400
- What'd you say to him?

37:20.467 --> 37:22.400
- Nothing.

37:22.467 --> 37:25.300
Nothing. Jeez.

37:25.367 --> 37:26.667
- Hey, you mick fucks.

37:26.734 --> 37:29.967
We're working over here.
You want to join us?

37:34.767 --> 37:36.834
- You know, I agonized
and agonized over telling you

37:36.900 --> 37:40.133
I saw Ryan O'Reily
murder Patrick Keenan.

37:40.200 --> 37:42.500
But finally, minister Said
convinced me to step forward,

37:42.567 --> 37:45.000
and yet O'Reily's
never been charged.

37:45.066 --> 37:46.600
- That's because I haven't
been able to gather

37:46.667 --> 37:48.834
any concrete evidence
against him.

37:48.900 --> 37:51.667
At this point, all I have
is your testimony,

37:51.734 --> 37:53.400
and you won't even
speak publicly.

37:53.467 --> 37:56.000
Or have you
changed your mind?

37:56.066 --> 37:57.967
- If I do, O'Reily
will have me killed.

37:58.033 --> 37:59.767
- Well, don't expect miracles.

37:59.834 --> 38:02.266
- You know, I've been going over
and over that moment in my mind,

38:02.333 --> 38:03.967
trying to remember
every detail.

38:04.033 --> 38:05.467
And this might not be
important, I don't know,

38:05.533 --> 38:06.667
but I think I saw O'Reily

38:06.734 --> 38:09.133
pull a shamrock
off of Keenan's neck.

38:11.333 --> 38:12.367
- A shamrock?

38:12.433 --> 38:14.500
- Yeah, a gold shamrock
on a chain.

38:14.567 --> 38:15.734
- I see.

38:15.800 --> 38:17.266
- Don't let this slide, Warden.

38:17.333 --> 38:18.934
Justice must be done.

38:19.000 --> 38:21.033
O'Reily must be punished.

38:22.667 --> 38:24.500
- Uh-uh, stay back.

38:24.567 --> 38:25.834
- But I've got a pain.

38:25.900 --> 38:27.266
-  Where?

38:27.333 --> 38:28.533
- In my heart.

38:28.600 --> 38:30.266
I'm heartsick
'cause you keep ignoring me.

38:30.333 --> 38:32.467
- I'm busy, Ryan.

38:35.734 --> 38:38.033
- I just wanted to know,
did the medical board--

38:38.100 --> 38:40.834
did they rule on your case
for malpractice?

38:43.834 --> 38:45.633
- Yes.

38:45.700 --> 38:48.467
They reprimanded me,
fined me,

38:48.533 --> 38:51.266
but I'm still a doctor.

38:51.333 --> 38:54.033
- Well, that's--
that's great, right?

38:55.000 --> 38:56.700
- Gloria?

38:58.467 --> 38:59.567
May I see you?

38:59.633 --> 39:01.166
- Sure.

39:02.400 --> 39:03.934
- Let's walk.

39:10.400 --> 39:12.967
Whoever killed Patrick Keenan
took a gold chain

39:13.033 --> 39:15.400
from around his neck,
a shamrock.

39:15.467 --> 39:17.800
At one point, when we spoke,

39:17.867 --> 39:19.333
you had a shamrock
in your hand.

39:19.400 --> 39:20.967
- It was his.

39:21.033 --> 39:22.533
- Where'd you get it?

39:22.600 --> 39:26.500
- Arrived one day at my office
in an unmarked envelope.

39:26.567 --> 39:28.033
- When I interviewed you
about the murder,

39:28.100 --> 39:30.033
why didn't you tell me
you had evidence?

39:30.100 --> 39:32.233
- Leo...

39:32.300 --> 39:34.166
I was raped.

39:34.233 --> 39:35.266
After a trauma like that,

39:35.333 --> 39:37.967
you're not always
thinking clearly.

39:38.033 --> 39:39.166
There are things that I've done
since that night

39:39.233 --> 39:40.767
that make no sense.

39:42.600 --> 39:44.667
Just when I think I've got
my feelings under control,

39:44.734 --> 39:48.700
the slightest thing
sets me off.

39:48.767 --> 39:51.900
- I know, and I'm sorry.

39:51.967 --> 39:55.467
- Honestly, there's a part of me
that's happy Keenan's dead.

39:55.533 --> 39:57.400
I just want to put his face
behind me.

39:57.467 --> 39:58.433
- Of course.

39:58.500 --> 40:01.633
Um, Gloria...

40:03.033 --> 40:05.867
One last question,
and I promise,

40:05.934 --> 40:07.567
I'll never bring it up again.

40:08.767 --> 40:10.133
Where's the necklace?

40:11.900 --> 40:13.300
- Here.

40:14.900 --> 40:16.567
I threw the fucking
thing away.

40:22.367 --> 40:23.700
- Oh, come on, Warden.

40:23.767 --> 40:25.300
There's got to be a rule
about the number of times

40:25.367 --> 40:27.934
you can keep on asking me
these same questions.

40:28.000 --> 40:30.567
- Do you think I'm screwing
with your civil rights?

40:30.633 --> 40:33.033
You want to
consult an attorney?

40:33.100 --> 40:35.066
- I don't need an attorney,
'cause I didn't kill Keenan.

40:35.133 --> 40:37.934
Look, man, check
the assignment records.

40:38.000 --> 40:40.734
I wasn't near the gym all day.

40:40.800 --> 40:42.166
- My informant
says different.

40:42.233 --> 40:43.200
- Your informant's a liar.

40:43.266 --> 40:45.700
- Why would he lie?

40:45.767 --> 40:49.033
- Look, a lot of people
got issues with me.

40:49.100 --> 40:50.600
A lot of people
had issues with Keenan.

40:50.667 --> 40:53.266
That kid was a scrapper.
He was in fights all the time.

40:53.333 --> 40:54.834
You go through the files,

40:54.900 --> 40:56.433
you'll find a shitload
of suspects.

40:57.633 --> 40:59.734
- I have.

40:59.800 --> 41:02.367
You're still the nearest
and the dearest.

41:03.967 --> 41:05.233
Take him out.

41:11.433 --> 41:13.633
- Glynn really wants to nail you
for Keenan's murder, huh?

41:13.700 --> 41:15.600
- He's got some witness,
only I don't know who.

41:15.667 --> 41:17.166
If I could only find out
this fucker's name,

41:17.233 --> 41:19.367
then I could persuade him
to change his testimony or...

41:19.433 --> 41:20.900
- Kill him?

41:20.967 --> 41:24.266
- Yeah, well, in any case,
I need to confuse the situation.

41:24.333 --> 41:28.200
- Yeah, I know.

41:28.266 --> 41:29.633
- This clipping.

41:29.700 --> 41:31.834
It needs to find its way
into Henry Stanton's trunk,

41:31.900 --> 41:34.166
buried beneath
his underwear.

41:34.233 --> 41:37.000
- Meanwhile, what are you
gonna be doing?

41:37.066 --> 41:38.767
- Encouraging an entirely
different eyewitness

41:38.834 --> 41:40.300
to step forward.

41:42.400 --> 41:44.233
- Whoa!
- Go, go! Go, Marty, go!

41:44.300 --> 41:46.033
Go! Go!

41:46.100 --> 41:47.900
- Come on!
- Yeah, baby!

41:47.967 --> 41:49.166
- Out!

41:49.233 --> 41:50.800
- What the fuck are you
talking about?

41:50.867 --> 41:53.467
I was right--
- You are out!

42:02.200 --> 42:06.000
- Prisoner number 99M633,

42:06.066 --> 42:08.000
Martin Montgomery,

42:08.066 --> 42:11.066
convicted March 16, 1999,

42:11.133 --> 42:13.133
two counts of assault
in the first degree.

42:13.200 --> 42:17.600
Sentence, eight years,
up for parole...

42:17.667 --> 42:19.567
in five.

42:23.233 --> 42:25.700
- Hey, Marty, my boy.

42:25.767 --> 42:27.133
How about another piece
of cake?

42:27.200 --> 42:29.066
- Sure, thanks.

42:29.133 --> 42:30.934
O'Reily, right?
- That's right.

42:31.000 --> 42:32.633
- How come you're
offering me extra cake?

42:32.700 --> 42:34.266
I've been here
almost three years.

42:34.333 --> 42:36.166
You never even farted
in my direction.

42:36.233 --> 42:38.266
- Well, you're right.
We're not friends.

42:38.333 --> 42:39.367
Everybody knows
we're not friends,

42:39.433 --> 42:40.467
which is why I can offer you

42:40.533 --> 42:42.233
an exciting money-making
opportunity.

42:42.300 --> 42:43.467
- Which is what?

42:43.533 --> 42:45.667
- I want you to
go to the warden

42:45.734 --> 42:47.533
and tell him
you saw Henry Stanton

42:47.600 --> 42:48.633
murder Patrick Keenan.

42:48.700 --> 42:50.367
- But I didn't.

42:50.433 --> 42:53.633
- Marty, there's a lot more cake
where that came from.

42:56.533 --> 43:00.800
- Stanton caught Keenan with
the barbell right about here.

43:00.867 --> 43:02.333
Keenan went down.

43:02.400 --> 43:04.467
Stanton ripped the necklace
from his throat.

43:04.533 --> 43:05.934
- What happened next?

43:06.000 --> 43:07.567
- I ran, I mean--

43:07.633 --> 43:10.567
what, I'm gonna
stick around?

43:10.633 --> 43:11.967
- All right.

43:12.033 --> 43:13.600
Thanks for coming forward.

43:15.100 --> 43:17.166
- Like I said, my conscience
couldn't take the strain

43:17.233 --> 43:19.300
of keeping what I saw inside.

43:22.767 --> 43:25.033
- I'll be damned.

43:25.100 --> 43:26.467
Normally,
nobody rats on anybody.

43:26.533 --> 43:28.000
Now I got
two different witnesses

43:28.066 --> 43:30.734
identifying two different
suspects for the same murder.

43:30.800 --> 43:33.200
- Well, Montgomery had
a lot more details than Arif.

43:33.266 --> 43:34.800
Specific details.

43:34.867 --> 43:38.333
- Yeah, and according
to the records,

43:38.400 --> 43:40.633
Stanton and Keenan
were constantly fighting.

43:43.066 --> 43:44.600
But why would Arif lie?

43:44.667 --> 43:45.934
- Ask him.

43:46.000 --> 43:47.633
- No.

43:47.700 --> 43:49.900
First I'm gonna have a word
with Henry Stanton.

43:53.367 --> 43:54.533
- Me?

43:54.600 --> 43:56.166
Kill Patrick Keenan?

43:56.233 --> 43:58.066
I wish.

43:58.133 --> 44:00.200
- At least twice
in Unit B,

44:00.266 --> 44:02.233
Keenan kicked the shit
out of you.

44:02.300 --> 44:05.033
- That ain't true.
I got my licks in.

44:05.100 --> 44:07.200
- Medical report...

44:07.266 --> 44:10.133
says after the first fight,
you had two broken ribs.

44:10.200 --> 44:12.367
The second one,
a broken wrist.

44:12.433 --> 44:15.333
Keenan had
no injuries at all.

44:15.400 --> 44:17.500
- Mine was a moral victory.

44:19.100 --> 44:20.834
- That day in the gym,

44:20.900 --> 44:22.433
you whacked him,
didn't you, Stanton?

44:22.500 --> 44:24.667
- No.

44:24.734 --> 44:27.233
I swear on my children, no.

44:29.600 --> 44:31.100
- We found this in your cell.

44:31.166 --> 44:34.233
- I've never even
seen this before.

44:34.300 --> 44:36.200
- You're obsessed
with Dr. Nathan, aren't you?

44:36.266 --> 44:37.800
- No.

44:37.867 --> 44:39.967
I mean, she's got nice tits
and all,

44:40.033 --> 44:41.266
but other than that,
I never even--

44:41.333 --> 44:42.433
- Take him to the Hole.

44:42.500 --> 44:43.767
- The Hole, why?

44:43.834 --> 44:46.667
- Maybe a few days there
will jostle your membrane.

44:46.734 --> 44:47.667
- Fuck you!

44:47.734 --> 44:48.800
Fuck you!

44:51.300 --> 44:52.233
Fuck you!

44:52.300 --> 44:54.400
Fuck you, you motherfuck!

44:56.600 --> 44:59.266
- Warden, how's
the investigation going?

44:59.333 --> 45:00.834
- Fine.

45:00.900 --> 45:03.633
- When are you
gonna charge O'Reily?

45:03.700 --> 45:05.433
- Let me ask you
something, Arif.

45:05.500 --> 45:09.100
Why are you so hell-bent
on Ryan O'Reily going down?

45:09.166 --> 45:11.734
- As I said,
justice must be done.

45:11.800 --> 45:13.433
- Mm-hmm, there's
no other reason?

45:13.500 --> 45:15.834
No other agenda?
- No.

45:15.900 --> 45:18.233
- As in payback for some wrong
done to you?

45:18.300 --> 45:20.433
- No.

45:20.500 --> 45:21.900
- I've been digging around.

45:21.967 --> 45:23.300
During the riots,
you and O'Reily

45:23.367 --> 45:24.767
almost came to blows.

45:24.834 --> 45:26.567
- The riot?

45:26.633 --> 45:27.934
That was five years ago.

45:28.000 --> 45:31.934
- In my experience,
cons have long memories.

45:32.000 --> 45:34.567
- You think I made
this story up?

45:34.633 --> 45:35.667
- You know what?

45:35.734 --> 45:37.800
At this point,
I don't know.

45:37.867 --> 45:40.533
And I'm beginning to wonder
if I even care.

45:50.233 --> 45:51.400
- Ready for this?

45:51.467 --> 45:53.066
Glynn suspended
the investigation

45:53.133 --> 45:54.500
into the murder
of Patrick Keenan.

45:54.567 --> 45:56.567
Too many suspects,
not enough clues.

45:56.633 --> 45:57.600
- Perfect.

45:57.667 --> 45:59.066
- Bet you could press it.

45:59.133 --> 46:00.800
Bet you could get
Stanton convicted.

46:00.867 --> 46:01.800
- Don't want to.

46:01.867 --> 46:03.033
- Why?

46:03.100 --> 46:04.567
- Look.

46:04.633 --> 46:06.266
Henry Stanton gets
the death penalty

46:06.333 --> 46:08.066
for Keenan's murder?

46:08.133 --> 46:10.200
Gloria Nathan's not gonna let
an innocent man die.

46:10.266 --> 46:12.967
She's gonna feel compelled
to tell the truth.

46:13.033 --> 46:16.433
No, I win
by keeping the ball in play,

46:16.500 --> 46:18.433
by keeping the facts murky.

46:20.967 --> 46:22.967
Have that placed
in Marty Montgomery's cell.

46:23.033 --> 46:24.133
- Montgomery?

46:24.200 --> 46:26.166
Why Montgomery?
- Life insurance.

46:29.467 --> 46:32.567
- Ryan, can I tell Henry
our secret?

46:32.633 --> 46:34.033
That we fooled
the warden?

46:34.100 --> 46:35.433
- No, Cyril,
for Chrissake,

46:35.500 --> 46:37.533
don't say a fucking word
to him!

46:38.767 --> 46:41.000
- Stop yelling.

46:41.066 --> 46:43.100
Why do you always yell?

46:43.166 --> 46:44.500
Like Papa.

46:48.533 --> 46:50.266
- Fuck off.

46:52.066 --> 46:54.166
- Galileo Galilei
challenged the principle

46:54.233 --> 46:56.633
that had been accepted
for over 1,000 years,

46:56.700 --> 46:59.033
that the Earth was
the center of the universe,

46:59.100 --> 47:01.734
that everything
revolved around us.

47:01.800 --> 47:04.900
The mad monks in the Inquisition
imprisoned Galileo

47:04.967 --> 47:09.433
and ordered him to repudiate
his theory, which he did.

47:09.500 --> 47:11.700
How much worse of a punishment
is there than being forced

47:11.767 --> 47:14.500
to publicly deny
your deepest beliefs,

47:14.567 --> 47:17.767
to say that what
you know to be true...

47:19.900 --> 47:21.533
Is a lie?

47:39.033 --> 47:40.633
- I see that baby over there

47:40.700 --> 47:43.033
and I can't help but think
about Augustus

47:43.100 --> 47:44.767
when he was just born,

47:44.834 --> 47:47.233
when he took his first step.

47:49.066 --> 47:51.633
You know, you think back
and say, "If I had done this",

47:51.700 --> 47:53.700
or, "If that hadn't happened",

47:53.767 --> 47:55.967
his whole life
might have been different.

47:56.033 --> 47:58.834
- Allah guides our every step.

47:58.900 --> 48:00.266
- I know.

48:00.333 --> 48:03.367
God is my rock,
but he can't stop

48:03.433 --> 48:05.233
the thoughts
from flooding my head,

48:05.300 --> 48:08.867
the memories from flowing.

48:08.934 --> 48:11.033
Augustus' first suit,

48:11.100 --> 48:13.200
his first day of school.

48:14.500 --> 48:16.433
Oh, his wedding day!

48:16.500 --> 48:18.734
He looked so happy.

48:18.800 --> 48:20.567
He and Annabella both did.

48:20.633 --> 48:22.867
The sun was
shining so bright,

48:22.934 --> 48:26.467
I had to squint my eyes
as they drove away.

48:26.533 --> 48:28.467
And now...

48:28.533 --> 48:31.166
I feel like I lost him
that day,

48:31.233 --> 48:32.867
in more ways than one.

48:34.734 --> 48:38.467
His--his world got narrower,
you know?

48:38.533 --> 48:40.600
With the drugs and all.

48:40.667 --> 48:42.567
- Is he still using?

48:42.633 --> 48:45.266
- Oh, no, thank God.

48:45.333 --> 48:48.567
My boy's been clean
over three years.

48:48.633 --> 48:50.433
I'm very proud of him
for that.

48:50.500 --> 48:52.200
- Yes, indeed.

48:53.433 --> 48:55.500
- And that's why I'm worried.

48:57.233 --> 48:59.700
That's why today
is gonna be so hard.

48:59.767 --> 49:01.367
I...

49:02.433 --> 49:04.867
I've got news
to tell him,

49:04.934 --> 49:07.300
bad news,

49:07.367 --> 49:09.800
news that I want him
to hear from me first,

49:09.867 --> 49:13.567
because maybe if I can just
cushion the blow,

49:13.633 --> 49:16.600
he--he won't go back
to the crack.

49:19.633 --> 49:22.967
His wife, Annabella--

49:23.033 --> 49:24.934
she's divorcing him.

49:25.000 --> 49:27.400
- Oh, my.

49:30.633 --> 49:33.433
- I tried talking
to the girl, but...

49:35.633 --> 49:37.767
Her mind's made up.

49:37.834 --> 49:41.233
She's got another fella, and...

49:41.300 --> 49:42.934
she wants to be free.

49:45.033 --> 49:47.800
And yet,

49:47.867 --> 49:49.633
God help me, I...

49:49.700 --> 49:51.934
I can't stop blaming her,

49:52.000 --> 49:57.400
for the darkness
in Augustus' life.

49:57.467 --> 49:59.567
She was with him...

50:00.834 --> 50:03.834
The night he shot
the policeman,

50:03.900 --> 50:07.600
the night his spine
got snapped.

50:10.367 --> 50:13.633
She should've taken
better care of my son.

50:19.533 --> 50:20.834
- Eugenia?

50:22.734 --> 50:25.333
Oh, I'm fine.

50:27.467 --> 50:29.500
I'm fine.

50:29.567 --> 50:31.266
I'm fine.

50:31.333 --> 50:34.633
The tears are for Augustus,
my little emperor.

50:38.934 --> 50:43.333
Locked in a cell
down in that wretched place.

50:45.567 --> 50:48.133
Half his body dead.

50:52.800 --> 50:54.667
And damn...

50:58.300 --> 51:01.200
All I keep thinking of

51:01.266 --> 51:03.400
is his first step.

51:07.133 --> 51:10.100
- Yo, Burr, how come you
don't never get in line?

51:11.700 --> 51:13.166
- 'Cause ain't nobody
sending me nothing.

51:13.233 --> 51:14.734
- You see this?

51:14.800 --> 51:16.934
Motherfuckers want me
to donate money

51:17.000 --> 51:20.233
to the United
Negro College Fund.

51:20.300 --> 51:22.200
They got to be kidding.

51:24.967 --> 51:26.734
- Fuck.

51:28.400 --> 51:31.500
It's a letter
from some lawyer.

51:31.567 --> 51:33.900
My wife's divorcing me.

51:33.967 --> 51:37.166
- Uh, is this a surprise?

51:37.233 --> 51:38.967
- No, I guess not.

51:39.033 --> 51:40.867
I mean--no, no.

51:40.934 --> 51:42.767
I mean, she--

51:42.834 --> 51:44.834
she been visiting me
less and less, you know.

51:44.900 --> 51:48.400
When she does come, there's...

51:48.467 --> 51:50.066
definitely a distance.

51:50.133 --> 51:52.000
- Well, what
do you expect?

51:52.066 --> 51:55.567
- You been cooped up here
in Oz for the last seven years.

51:55.633 --> 51:56.934
That's a long time

51:57.000 --> 51:58.567
for a young gal
to keep a candle lit.

51:58.633 --> 51:59.867
- I know.

51:59.934 --> 52:02.100
It's just that--

52:02.166 --> 52:04.700
you know,
we loved each other.

52:04.767 --> 52:05.767
The least Annabella
could've done

52:05.834 --> 52:07.734
was come and said good-bye.

52:07.800 --> 52:09.166
- It's tough luck,
Augustus.

52:09.233 --> 52:11.533
Man, it's tough
fucking luck.

52:13.300 --> 52:16.400
- You'll survive, son.

52:16.467 --> 52:17.834
You survived this shithole.

52:17.900 --> 52:20.033
You'll survive a divorce.

52:21.266 --> 52:22.900
- Maybe.

52:25.867 --> 52:29.800
It's like, losing her, it's--

52:29.867 --> 52:32.000
it's like giving up
my last piece of hope.

52:33.767 --> 52:35.133
It's like admitting
to myself

52:35.200 --> 52:38.667
that everything
I had out there is gone.

52:39.934 --> 52:42.033
It's gone forever.

52:45.567 --> 52:48.333
- You know, I never
told you this, but...

52:48.400 --> 52:51.100
Dee and I was fixing
to divorce too.

52:51.166 --> 52:53.600
- What?
- Just before she got sick.

52:55.333 --> 52:57.767
Course, after she got sick,
I couldn't leave her then.

52:57.834 --> 53:00.233
- But I thought you and Dee
was happy.

53:00.300 --> 53:01.834
You always seemed so happy.

53:01.900 --> 53:04.433
- That was the vodka.

53:04.500 --> 53:08.233
Only woman I knew that could
drink more liquor than me.

53:08.300 --> 53:13.100
That love in her eyes was
always a little bit blurry.

53:13.166 --> 53:14.233
No, you and your moms

53:14.300 --> 53:15.900
was the only real family
I ever knew.

53:17.734 --> 53:19.233
- She's coming today.

53:20.667 --> 53:23.367
- Eugenia.

53:23.433 --> 53:25.633
- Maybe you and me
could visit Mom together.

53:31.633 --> 53:33.400
- You know,
I'd like that.

53:35.934 --> 53:38.066
I'd like to see Eugenia.

53:41.433 --> 53:44.433
She always had
the sweetest pair of eyes.

54:02.667 --> 54:05.100
- Okay, it looks like we're
gonna be at the main gate

54:05.166 --> 54:07.367
of Oswald
in about five minutes.

55:06.500 --> 55:09.400
Sonsyrea Arif,

55:09.467 --> 55:11.500
Charles Balis,

55:11.567 --> 55:13.667
Eugenia Hill...

55:15.133 --> 55:17.266
Sandy Laitman,

55:17.333 --> 55:19.633
Annette Osorio,

55:19.700 --> 55:22.033
Shirin Patel,

55:22.100 --> 55:24.066
Joanie Ranzer,

55:24.133 --> 55:26.233
Carrie Schillinger.

55:26.300 --> 55:28.667
- What about my granddaughter?

55:28.734 --> 55:30.767
Jewel Schillinger?

55:30.834 --> 55:32.000
- She's at Benchley Memorial.

55:32.066 --> 55:33.200
She's in stable condition.

55:34.967 --> 55:36.633
David Swanson...

55:38.667 --> 55:40.100
Pamela Turton...

55:41.567 --> 55:43.467
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

55:43.533 --> 55:45.266
Lots of fine people
have sat,

55:45.333 --> 55:47.967
staring at the inside
of prison walls,

55:48.033 --> 55:50.734
Socrates, Gandhi,
Joan of Arc,

55:50.800 --> 55:54.233
even our Lord,
Jesus Christ.

55:54.300 --> 55:56.200
He spent the last night
of his life

55:56.266 --> 55:58.734
not with holy men,
but with scum,

55:58.800 --> 56:01.100
like the kind
we got in Oz.

56:01.166 --> 56:03.100
One of the last things
Jesus did on Earth

56:03.166 --> 56:07.100
was invite a prisoner
to join him in heaven.

56:08.834 --> 56:11.433
He loved that criminal.

56:11.500 --> 56:16.667
I say he loved that criminal
as much as he loved anyone.

56:16.734 --> 56:18.800
Jesus knew in his heart,

56:18.867 --> 56:20.967
it takes a lot
to love a sinner.

56:21.033 --> 56:24.066
But the sinner...

56:24.133 --> 56:25.700
he needs it all the more.
